Parliament, Monday, 26 August 2019 – The Standing Committee on Finance and the Select Committee on Finance will this week conduct oversight visits to the South African Revenue Services (Sars) and the South African Reserve Bank in Gauteng. The committees will also meet with the Public Investment Corporation (PIC), Government Employees Pension Fund (GEPF) and the Government Pensions Administration Agency (GPAA). These meetings will take place at the Sars offices. Details of the oversight are as follows: Tuesday 27 August
	Venue: Sars Head Office
	Time: 09H00 Wednesday 28 August
	Venue: South African Reserve Bank Conference Centre
	Time: 09H00 Media wishing to cover the oversight visit should confirm with Sakhile Mokoena: smokoena@parliament.gov.za / 081 705 2130 and for the South African Reserve Bank copy Liesel Radebe on media@resbank.co.za or 012 313 4754. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE STANDING COMMITTEE ON FINANCE, MR JOE MASWANGANYI AND THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE SELECT COMMITTEE ON FINANCE MR YUNUS CARRIM. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact the committees’ Media Officer: Name: Sakhile Mokoena
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 2804
	Cell: 081 705 2130
